text: I do not understand all the people I've seen talking about how good [[Yavimaya Hollow]] is lately. I mean, there's probably some U/G draw-go type deck where it's handy, but I ran it for a long time in quite a few decks and it was rarely ever effective.
something something reserve list staple something
I'm sure that's a huge part of it
But it makes colorless mana for your eldrazi!!!0
OP

It's just the conversation seems different about Hollow. People actively seem to be saying repeatedly that it's really good. I wonder how many of them have actually ran it? I get that it looks good on paper, but it's hardly ever a good idea to leave two mana free on the off-chance the board wipe or removal spell you fear isn't an exile and doesn't have a "can't be regenerated" clause.
Yea, it's a fine utility card, but it's definitely not a must play in any deck
A buddy of mine runs it in his Thrun deck and kind of has the same reaction you're talking about. I guess redundancy?
I guess
Gotta watch out for that [[pithing needle]] I guess
